cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the impact of publication modalities on the average citation of scientific journals, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the dissemination and management of digital information, including publication practices. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as it deals with the retrieval and analysis of information from large datasets, which includes citation analysis. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are less likely but still possible as they both involve the analysis of large datasets and the evaluation of research impact. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possibility as it deals with the analysis of information dissemination and impact in social networks.
